{
  "text": "A first result showed that quite a high proportion of subjects failed to detect any change (71.4%). This is a rather high proportion considering (1) that observers had been instructed to focus on the faces of the actors and to memorize them; (2) that facial expressions are highly salient stimuli that are socially relevant in all cultures [CITATION_1] ).",
